  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 960 mg
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1} into strips. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a small #pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add @peanuts{1/2%ounce}, 2 TBSP water, and @sugar{1%tsp}. Cook, stirring often, until water has evaporated and peanuts are coated and lightly toasted, ~{3-5%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a small #bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and onion; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until tender and lightly browned, ~{6-9%minutes}. Transfer veggies to a #plate{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @diced chicken thighs{10%ounce}; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in veggies, then add @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and @butter{1%tbsp}. Cook, stirring, until mixture is thoroughly coated, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and lime zest to taste. Season with salt. Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with chicken mixture, peanuts, and cilantro. Serve with lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.

> For 4 servings, increase water to 2 1/4 cups, and increase sugar and butter quantities accordingly.